homedescription: New construction house in the heart of Ballard. Great open floor plan with large master bedroom loft. Vaulted ceilings with tons of light, modern styling and finishes. Tasteful gourmet kitchen with stainless steel appliances. Beautifully tiled bathrooms. Concrete and bamboo floors, plus radiant heat flooring. Ahhh the radiant heat floors! Private assigned off street parking. Desirable Ballard location, walk to shops and restaurants. A whopping walking score of 94! The kitchen and baths are not the red you see but a creamy chartreuse. The property now also includes a 400 square foot outdoor fully tiled entertainment patio with a privacy fence, trees in commercial pots and modern french doors in place of the basic sliding door. Just open the doors and you have an entire outdoor room. The builders didn't cut corners and made this a bright, comfortable and luxurious place to live.
whatownerloves: Great use of space, feels much bigger than its 900 sq ft. The interior and exterior are made with quality materials and the builders were meticulious about building a solid, square and high quality house. What can I say about radiant heat floors! They keep the house warm with no nasty noise or "stuff" floating through the air. The builders added lots of extra touches including lighting in really great places. The short walk to "all things Ballard" is awesome. I leave the car at home all weekend. It is also close to local parks and even though it's blocks from Market Street, the neighborhood is incredibly quiet. I've also had a 400 square foot outdoor patio professionally tiled with 2'x'2' concrete tiles. It's like an extra large room outdoors. Perfect for summer parties. There's no up-keep, just clean the house and go! Also this is a HOUSE, not a townhouse or condo. No dues, you own the property as well.

homedescription:
This is a rare, large rambler, over 3,000 sq feet located in Bellevue. Nestled among multi-million dollar homes, this house has been completely remodeled - updated everything, but kept the 1937 charm. Fantastic views of the lake from every room - listen to lake waves, watch eagles daily, see all the action on the lake, and enjoy the fireworks over Lake Sammamish from the porch every July 4th. Put your boat in at Vasa Park down the street & park it in the houses gated boat parking. New wing addition with new kitchen including kitchen nook and Family room/Den with new gas fireplace. Kitchen is light & bright with granite counter-tops, Thermador gas stove, new sinks/faucets, hardware, and new designer tiled back splash. Adjacent Dining Room & formal Living Room have cove ceilings and arched entry's. Original hardwoods throughout the house, recently refinished. Master Bedroom wing boasts sweeping views of the lake (as does every room in the house). 3 fireplaces -2 wood burning, 1 gas with new Gas insert. Stone for fireplaces was dredged from Lake Sammamish in the 1930's. Completely renovated downstairs (down to the studs) has 2 large bedrooms, full bathroom, and large living/play area. Also, a 400 sq ft Storage area & built in heated Workshop / Hobby area. Wine storage unit. Brand new Cold Air Conditioning keeps you cool through the summer. 
Home is on .33 acre with large level front and back yard. Mature landscaping in the English cottage style. Beautiful rose garden and vegetable garden. Automated sprinkler system. Several Fruit trees : apple, cherry, blueberry & plum tree. 2 car garage. Large stand alone shop, as well as boat / RV storage on gated property with own gate to Parkway. Whole house air filtration system installed in 2009 & Central Air Conditioning newly installed. Newer roof. Just installed new deck (2014), twice as large as that pictured. Contact me via email for showing. Home is not MLS listed. Please know that I am not looking for any realtor representation at this time, thank you!
whatownerloves: This home has charm that is rarely found in Bellevue. It is truly a gem with a vacation feeling all year long - views are amazing. Stay-cation all year round. When you enter the gated area, you feel like you are in a private reserve. Privet & gate, gives privacy. No noise from W Lk Samm.

homedescription:
Neighborhood Description  Zoned L3.  

This is a historical neighborhood among mansions of early Seattle.
Just blocks from the famous Volunteer Park and all  Broadway has to offer.





 Welcome to A unique Oasis in the City of Seattle on Capitol Hill. It was built in 1929, Rooms are oversized with hardwood floors dressed up with oriental carpets. The original Spa like bathroom has leaded glass arched windows overlooking lush majestic palm trees. Very European, with all original tile, spa tub for your relaxation.



 In your spacious lounge, living area you have a brand new leather sofa where you can read, relax or watch television.



 You can set at your dining table with your Seattle's Famous Coffee, or sip a glass of local wine while working on your lap top or just trying to decide what you want to do. So much to do, So little time...... There are large windows that let in more than ample sunlight.



 If you don't wish to dine out in one of the many great restaurants, many in close walking distance, you can prepare your meal in your very own European inspired kitchen. There you will find everything you need but the food.



 The bedroom is very cozy and there is plenty of closet area.



 If you don't have all you need, let us know so we can work on getting it for you.
 JUST BLOCKS FROM MAJOR HOSPITALS.

 JUST 2 Blocks from the Famous Beautiful Volunteer Park, Conservatory. Asian Art Museum, Cal Anderson Park. This Beautiful Home is Located in the Heartbeat of Seattle's CAPITOL HILL. This Seattle Four Square is charming!  The main living area is open and spacious and includes a dining room and family room with a view of the Ballard Bridge, Discovery Park, and Olympic Mountains.  The kitchen is spacious with plenty of cabinet space and a recently added pantry.  There is also plenty of space for an informal dining table.  There are three bedrooms on the top floor.  One bedroom has a windowed nook with a view of a 100 year old cedar just outside the window.  There are high ceilings throughout the house.

There have been updates most notably a mother in law apartment in the basement that is bright and cheery and has full amenities including a washer and dryer.   

Important design elements have been kept including the original fir floors, molding and windows, which add warmth to the overall feel of the house.  
Additional updates include the installation of an energy efficient heat pump with split level heating /cooling system, a stairway to the attic with reinforced flooring for storage, radiant heated tiled bathroom floor, and a washer and dryer on the bedroom level.

The yard is enclosed and has a fountain which creates a garden refuge in the hustle and bustle of city life.
whatownerloves:
Five generations have lived in this house.  They have raised kids, celebrated holidays with friends and family and had many happy days.  It is a warm and wonderful place to live.  

It is in the heart of three amazing communities; Fremont, Ballard and Phinney Ridge.  Each neighborhood has a unique personality and there are so many opportunities to get out and explore including; outdoor markets, seasonal celebrations, unique artisan products and fresh produce. homedescription:
Updated rambler located on beautiful convenient Rose Hill in Kirkland! 

Live in the perfect family friendly walkable neighborhood, with a great school district. 

This bright sunny updated home welcomes you with warm hickory hardwoods floors and modern LED lighting throughout.  It has many added green features including improved insulation and convenient tech upgrades like WiFi enabled thermostats and lights, touchscreen keypad door locks, and USB chargers built into the wall outlets.

Come on in.  Open the solid wood front door to an entryway with skylight and coat closet.   Move into the adjoining bright sunny living room, where you find a natural stone hearth, a thermostatically controlled gas fireplace, and a wall-mounted TV.  The adjacent dining room connects with a remodeled kitchen.  We redesigned things to make extra space and in the process added new granite counters and sink, a tile back-splash, additional cabinets, new overhead and under-cabinet lighting, and new appliances including a particularly super exhaust fan.   

From the kitchen, pass through multi-light French doors out onto the 170-sq foot deck where you can enjoy one of the few territorial views in Rose Hill.  Just watch your garden grow or eat your meal as the sun sets over the Olympic Mountains.  

All three bedrooms have hickory floors, ample closet space and daylight. The two tile floor baths have plenty of light and updated hardware.  The new shower head is the best I've ever found.  There is an attached two-car garage, a laundry room with granite, extensive storage, and new HardiePlank shingle siding and trim outside (warrantee through 2045, included).  

Also outdoors, you are situated on a 9,880 square foot Rose Hill lot, with new landscaping, a mature ever-bearing raspberry patch, a large terraced vegetable garden, fruit trees and a big open back yard.  Yes, the garden and backyard get full sunshine.  

This place allows for simple, low maintenance, carefree living.   All-in-all, a delightful place to call home.  It could be a great place for you to create new memories!
whatownerloves: We remodeled in 2015!  Kitchen redone; granite counters, granite sink, high stone backslash, new brushed steel (stainless) appliances, gas stove, cork floor in laundry, thermostatically controlled gas fireplace, gas to deck for a BBQ, LED lighting and in-wall USB outlets throughout, electronic entry, wifi thermostat, new hot-water heater, new skylights, and new attic and crawlspace insulation.  We also created a large terraced full-sun garden, added fruit trees and a large covered outdoor work area in the backyard!  It's a fun convenient  turn-key place, with indoor and outdoor living.

homedescription: Paradise presents itself on prestigious yet private Perkins Lane. This spacious waterfront residence takes full advantage of its southwest facing orientation, enjoys lush verdant landscaping with winding paths to the beach & boasts panoramic and unrivaled views of the Puget Sound, Mount Rainier & Olympic Mountains. Grand formal living & dining rooms flow to the sunroom all basking in warm southern views and highlighted by hardwood floors, cove ceilings, classic millwork and a period fireplace with marble surround. The kitchen is generous in size, designed with functionality in mind and offers excellent counter & cupboard space w/island breakfast bar, updated appliance package, wood burning stove, desk area and access to the rear patio & artists studio with 3/4 bath. The upper floor offers two spacious view bedrooms serviced by a full bath accented in travertine stone and a cozy water closet. The bedrooms enjoy access through French doors to the expansive deck terrace. Garage access is also located on this floor. Finished lower level offers rec/media room with stone fireplace & sunroom, two bedrooms serviced by a 3/4 bath and access to three large storage areas and the beach. If your interests involve boating, fishing, crabbing, beachcombing, camp fires and watching beavers, otters, salmon, whales & eagles this home offers a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity that must not be missed! Also offers a full 2 plus car garage with plenty of on-street parking and is conveniently located to the Village, schools, shopping, parks, Pop Mounger pool, Interbay golf facility, I-5 and downtown Seattle.

New custom wood blinds, new custom cellular shades, new custom energy efficient shades. homedescription:
An airy, open, home with high ceilings and three fireplaces. Built by an architect in 1990, the home takes full advantage of the sloped lot and has three levels, all east facing. The house has been well maintained and has a neutral palette throughout. Completely updated in 2014.  The kitchen has Viking stainless steel appliances and a U Line dual temperature wine fridge, slab granite counters with a porcelain tiled back splash, huge stainless steel sink and touch activated faucet. Fully functional laundry room with deep sink and lots of cupboards make laundry days easy.  A tankless hot water system and two furnaces keep the house warm in winter, and air conditioning cools when needed in summer.  Oak flooring on main living level, neutral carpets in all bedrooms, with marble tiles/granite in master bathroom, guest bathroom and entrance hall, travertine tiles/granite in children's and second guest bathroom, as well as the laundry. The guest suite, with bathroom,  has a beautiful, private porch and a separate entrance, wonderful for in-laws or an au pair.

homedescription: Value is in the waterfront land and south-facing views of Lake Washington and Mt. Rainier. Existing cottage is a tear-down or possible major remodel, with neighboring new-builds at $4M - $7M. Dominant view is of Mt. Rainier, unobstructed. Property is at the extreme south point of Mercer Island, where the docks are built far apart; over 80' separation on each side. View looks across 2 miles of Lake Washington to Coulon Beach Park and Boeing on the opposite shore. The Boeing plant is part of the view: 1/2 the relative height of the hills forming the southern horizon, and 1/4 the relative height of Mt. Rainer (see last photo). 60' dock with 12'x24' grandfathered platform. Lake access via steps and swim ladder. No steep driveway; carport sits directly on the dead-end public street with 4 spaces, off-street, side-by-side. Access road is a quiet, public street, recently paved. Boat lift is being sold, but easy to permit. For Seahawk fans, the VMAC training facility can be seen in the distance from the dock. Mercer Island Beach Club is 1/4 mile east. No listing calls please. Owner will work with Buyer's Agents. This home is not actively listed for sale through Zillow or any brokerage.

homedescription: This Burnstead home is located in the desirable Brighton Place on Education Hill. It offers all the conveniences of living in Redmond, with the serenity of the surrounding natural trail in front of the home and pond preserve in the back. Summers are spent entertaining on the back decks enjoying sunsets, hot air balloons in flight, croaking frogs and chirping birds.  The main floor includes the master with 2 piece bath, laundry room, powder room, formal living and dining areas, office, kitchen and family room. The basement has  three bedrooms with one large enough to serve as a second master, a full bath, living area, second office, media room, and craft or exercise room. The finished sub-basement acts as a 700 square foot accessory dwelling unit (mother-in-law) with separate entrance, 3/4 bath, one bedroom, washer/dryer and kitchen furnished in stainless appliances, granite and travertine finishes.  The garage houses 3 vehicles and enough storage for all the tools as well as a shop area. The home is equipped with two security systems, in-wall speaker system, 3-car garage and leaf guard gutters.
whatownerloves: What I love about this home are the beautiful sunsets off the two large back decks, luxurious finishes, spacious rooms, quality craftsmanship and friendly neighborhood. There is plenty of room for a large family or multi-generational living, and a separate dwelling for guests, extended family members or income potential. homedescription:
Located next to Idylwood Park Beach. 2 bedroom/ 2 bathrooms 1100+ Sq ft Condo. Carport. Freshest Air and Tastiest Water on tap. Relatively ordinary interior with some nice touches.  Walking distance to Microsoft. Kitchen, dining, living area with some Lake View.   Next to jog, bike paths and bus stand.  The city maintains your lovely backyard/ beach and only asks that you share it with a few people (a lot during summer time). 

Neighborhood Description

Beautiful scenic ("Viewpoint") neighborhood!  Take 520 here get off on NE 40th, walk around Idylwood park, drive along West Lake Sammamish and to the Shops at Redmond Center.  Drive around Marymoor Park. Cirque du Soleil, films and concerts play at Marymoor. This is one of the most affordable homes available in a top neighborhood thanks to ancient management problems--however anthropologists have cleared away the cavemen/women/saber-tooths.  2 New Medical clinics opened in the city.  Drive around it looks like a well-managed city! Courteous neighbors and drivers on the road.  Microsoft is one of 4 companies in the USA to have 'AAA' rating---higher than the U.S Govt!  This area has been a treasure in good times and a haven in the bad.  Commute to Amazon, Nintendo wii, Starbucks, Costco, even Zillow, big orders at Boeing, small medical companies. This part of the country is getting hotter...don't wait too long.
whatownerloves: Lots!  Drive around this area and experience it for yourself. Fast and Scenic (snow-capped mtns) commutes on the Eastside (Big Deal here). and moderate Summers, Serene Winters, sports in Spring and Fall.  Quiet and Peaceful.  Clean air and water on tap. Close to Marymoor Park with its tennis courts, baseball and soccer fields. Watch the rowing team on the lake.  Walking up the hill on NE40th is good exercise.  Idylwood Beach Parking is never a problem if you live here (carport parking). Great value!  Great as first home: accomodates some expansion, low maintenance, stable or growing area businesses.  Idylwood beach has a sandy not rocky beach...tan comfortably in your sand castle.

homedescription:
*This is a warm home that may be best in the development as it was completely remodeled right after taking possession of it as a brand new home!  Remodeling costs ran $40K on materials and stainless steel appliances.  The work was overseen and completed by myself except for tile work in the shower and master bath floor.
*This home comes with a very-well funded HOA reserve of over $500K (for 48 units) that covers everything for the next 20+ years except for utilities (including water/sewer), insurance, and landscaping which is covered by HOA dues of $310 month.
* Travel time to downtown Seattle is only 30 minutes.
* Hardwood maple cabinets in kitchen, 3 bathrooms, 4 in laundry room, and 5 in walk-in closet.  
* Maple laminate flooring in kitchen, downstairs bath, Breakfast Nook,  and entry.  Tile in master bath and toilet.  
* Built in Queen "Murphy" bed in guest room.
* Exterior repainted in 2013 and interior in 2014.   
* Condo has a private back patio area for entertaining with large newer stainless steel BBQ.    
* This unit has a large walk-in, tiled shower for two with 2 shower heads.
* The garage has two 8ft work tables, 5 wall cabinets, and over 100 feet of shelving.
* Garage is fully insulated.
* Crown molding and larger new base boards in the great room, master bed, bath. toilet and down stair bath rooms.
* Doggie door to the fenced back yard.
* All construction steps were inspected throughout by me and all work was done correctly.  I did most of the remodeling.
* Great room includes kitchen, dining, living, and area that can be used for office or formal dining.  
* The unit would accommodate a fold down "lift" to the second floor from the entry way with minor renovation in case I or you needed it.
whatownerloves:
* The Great Room - Living, dining, kitchen, office.
* Laundry room w/sink, washer, dryer, and four maple cabinets.
* Stainless; gas range, fridge, sink, big newer BBQ, micro wave, and dish washer.
* There is FREE access to many sports courts including: basketball, volleyball, tennis courts, soccer fields, and many other amenities like: parks and playgrounds is included in our master development agreement. 
* A golf course (Trilogy) is two blocks away.  
* A gym is three blocks away.
* Local QFC Market (two blocks away), and six good places to eat are less than five blocks away.  Two are award winners. 
* Has a very-well funded HOA reserve adding $10K to this home value.
* Parking for four cars - two smaller cars in the garage and two in large cars front of garage.
* A lot of Wildlife. 
* A Green Belt to the back. 
* Instant Hot Water in kitchen.  
* Has a large newer stainless BBQ worth $1.5K.
* We have underground power all the way to the power sub station, so have been without power only 8 hours total in the last 9 years. 
* Lots of storage under stairs and in garage, and Attic.

homedescription:
This three bedroom, two bath is one of the few of the larger floor plans in Sixty 01 Village, a secure and gated complex that prides itself in providing residents with a myriad of amenities including but not limited to swimming pools, tennis and volleyball courts, a fitness center, a fully equipped clubhouse that can be reserved for special occasions, a cluster of beautiful picnic and BBQ locations, miles of private pathways adorned with well maintained flora, and three serene lakes filled with carp, sunfish, and a family of ducks. 

The entry of the condo is characterized by a set of double doors, perfect for transporting larger pieces of furniture in and out. Polished hardwood floors line the entryway and extend to the corridor, kitchen, and dining room. An assortment of quaint features such as a lazy Susan in one of the kitchen cupboards, track lighting in the bedroom and living room, and full length mirrors on all the bedroom closet doors add a level of uniqueness and distinguishment to the home. The living room, master bedroom, and one of the auxiliary rooms are all connected to private balconies. Each room enjoys spaciousness and ceiling to floor windows which further integrate the condo into the natural beauty directly outside. Speaking of natural beauty, the dozens of trees which surround the unit not only contribute to the seclusion and privacy of the condo, but also keep the interior cool even on Seattle's hottest days. With a walk-in closet in the master, another in the living room, as well as a storage unit in the building lobby provided by Sixty 01 alongside two covered parking spaces, storage is not likely to be an issue.
whatownerloves: The location, right in the heart of Bridle Trails, is perfection. A bus stop sits directly at the entrance of Sixty 01, just a few minutes walk away from this particular unit. This provides for an exceptionally easy and stress free commute to Microsoft, or even farther to Seattle Downtown or the UW. A few blocks down the street is a small shopping complex which includes a grocery store, drug store, and Starbucks.

homedescription: One-of-a-Kind secluded one level home on 2.5 acres in East Redmond. Property has park-like grounds with several water features and many bearing fruit trees (apple, pear, pie cherries). Two-car attached garage as well as a separate large three-car/shop building with separate electrical billing for possible business use. Fenced in garden area to keep out deer and rabbits. A cottage-like garden house that could be used as a playhouse as well. A sizeable woodshed is nestled at the edge of the woods to support your unique Russian fireplace (requires less wood). Central vacuum, air conditioning, electronic air cleaner. Super large kitchen with solid oak cabinets, subzero refrigerator and freezer, two new skylights, granite island, peninsula, open to large family room with beautiful sunroom wall, fireplace and newly refinished hardwood flooring. Vaulted ceilings throughout most of the house. Step-down living room enclosed with a single and a double-French leaded-glass door for possible use as media room. Built in counter/cabinetry on one wall. The master bedroom opens out onto a concrete aggregate patio with an overhead wisteria-covered arbor leading to a covered gazebo with ironwood deck. A short curved sidewalk leads to another large covered deck off the family room with hot tub and natural gas barbecue. Master bathroom also features a glass-enclosed shower and large corner spa tub (no jets), and double sinks (one sink larger with shampoo sprayer). Master bedroom has his and her walk-in closets and high ceilings. Will consider selling master bedroom custom furniture with home. A second large bedroom has a nice walk in shampoo sink area and walk-in closet and exterior access onto a small patio. Third bedroom has walk-in closet as well. Very large laundry room with large sink, accessible from garage as mudroom. RV parking with nearby RV electrical hookup. New furnace in last 3 years, brand new roof last year with 25 year guarantee and all sunroom windows replaced last year. Home is in the sought-after Lake Washington school district.
whatownerloves: Quiet secluded privacy and connection with nature as if stepping into a different world.  Ideal for entertainment with the large covered hot tub deck area with natural gas barbecue.  The one level design also makes it ideal for retirement couples.  A back bedroom with adjoining bathroom can be blocked off for a mother-in-law suite as it has its own sliding glass door entrance onto a small patio.  A kitchen with enough cabinetry and space for a couple to both cook to their heart's desire without interfering with each other.  The kitchen open to the family room allows guests to socialize with the chefs as well.  Green Beauty out every window.

homedescription: Located in one of the best 55 & older mobile home parks on the Eastside, this bright and cheerful 2 bedroom mobile home is in terrific move-in condition! There's a new metal roof with insulation. Also new is the exterior paint, deck carpets, bathroom toilets, sinks & faucets. The kitchen has attractive oak cabinets and a gas stove. Washer, dryer & refrigerator are included. The floor plan is really nice with the large utility room conveniently in the back portion of the home. There's a free-standing gas stove in the large living room. Outside there's 2 storage sheds and a big covered deck. This terrific mobile home sits on an extra large corner lot and it is low maintenance. Friendly Village Mobile Home Park is a wonderful place to live. There's a community swimming pool, scenic areas to stroll or have a picnic. The community clubhouse has 2 pool tables, a kitchen, an exercise room, laundry room, and more! The park has planned activities at the clubhouse and bus trips too. People living here have the privacy of having their own mobile home & when they want to socialize they just have to go on a stroll to meet up with very friendly, kind neighbors.

homedescription:
Modern, cozy and private 2 bed/2 bath top floor - end unit condo - 900 sqft conveniently located near Redmond Town Center and Microsoft Campus. Luxury finishes include granite slab counters, modern wood cabinets, subway tile backsplash, and stainless steel GE appliances in kitchen, full W/D, premium bamboo hardwood flooring through out entire home including bedrooms, nice use of premium tiles, modern real-wood cabinets and chrome accents in bathrooms including elongated toilets, and 2 reserved parking spaces right outside your home, along with generous guest parking.

The feel of this home and community is best described similar to like staying at a modern lodge in Whistler Village, B.C. It's beautiful in the summer and cozy in the winter. This home is conveniently located on the east side central to a 5-10 minute drive time to downtown Bellevue, Kirkland Waterfront, and Woodinville (Wine Valley). Includes a community lodge with gym, media/event room, kitchenette, and outdoor patio with gas BBQ grill and an inviting fire pit.


Some Highlights:

* Modern architectural style and luxury finishes
* Top floor corner/end unit (3rd Floor) - with vaulted ceilings
* Surrounded by both broadleaf and pine trees providing beautiful year round nature views and virtually 100% privacy from other neighbors
* Daily sunrise drenches into the living room and master bedroom. Lot of natural light in all rooms
* Beautiful vaulted ceilings, wood burning fireplace, outside deck, and insulated double pane windows
* Includes double cell window shades for insulation and additional privacy
* Premium bamboo hardwood flooring throughout entire home including both bedrooms (no carpet)
* Spice pantry installed in kitchen and built-in kitchen bar counter open to living room
* Bedrooms are separate from each other and do not share a wall
* Nobody above you and only one small shared wall with the only other neighbor on top floor
* Master bath in master bedroom. Luxury elongated toilets
* Wired for tv cable in all rooms
* 2 dedicated parking spaces right out side home
* Attached storage closet outside by deck
* Water/Sewer/Garbage included in HOA dues
* 2-3 minutes away from 520 on-ramp and bus line to downtown Seattle.
* Minutes away from Woodinville (Wine Country), Kirkland Waterfront, Downtown Bellevue/Bellevue Square, Redmond Town Center, Marymoor Park & Dog Park, Lake Sammamish, Burke Gilman Trail, and more!

For a private showing appointment, please contact me via Zillow.
whatownerloves:
Corner top floor unit with 6 out of the 7 windows all featuring beautiful views of trees creating natural privacy without needing to use the blinds. Feels like a cozy winter lodge in the winter when snow has fallen covering the trees. Absolutely beautiful!

The morning sunrise and sunset light gushing into the home due to the unit being in the corner and on the top floor at same level as the tip top of the trees.

Both the master and guest bedrooms have been upgraded with the same beautiful bamboo hardwood floors.

Vaulted ceilings in the living room allows for taller bookshelves giving it a grander airier feel than lower units.

Great walkability to shopping, restaurants, Redmond Town Center mall in downtown Redmond.

Gym with treadmill, elliptical, and free weights is a nice plus!

Sunny Gorgeous Somerset Home ready for Move-In!
Airy Somerset home with Open floor plan and lots of Skylights that you MUST SEE!
This gorgeous home is an spacious 3bdr, 2.5 bath home in the best school district in the region - Somerset.

The home is remodeled by the renown Northwest architect Mike Lifton. It has a brand new kitchen with granite countertops and state of the art appliances and a gas burner and brand new top-of-the-line Washer Dryer (stays with house). It also has new hardwood floors and designer paint in natural tones, unique detailing that includes 2 fireplaces and expansive skylights. It is a tri-level, with three bedrooms on the upper floor, an expansive living room that opens out to a large deck, and a lower level den with functional wood-burning stove. The master bedroom has in-suite bathroom and a large walk-in closet. The backyard features an herb garden, fire pit and hot tub. 

The house is located in Somerset, one of the oldest, nicest neighborhoods in the Eastside. The house is walking distance from highly ranked Somerset Elementary, and very close to Tyee Middle School and Newport High School. Located near highways I-405 and I-90 means you dont have to pay toll to go to Seattle! The house is 3 minutes away from Expedia and Microsoft Advanta, 11 mins from Microsoft's main campus and just 15 mins from Seattle. It is also very close to the factoria shopping district and just a 10 minute drive to downtown Bellevue. 

The house comes with Washer/Dryer, Fridge, Dishwasher and a gorgeous Hot Tub. The house also has a security system and is wired for cable/internet/wireless.

My neighbors are poster children for State Farm :) Never expected such a cool neighborhood where people really really care about their houses, their gardens and lawns and the neighborhood. Also, the stunning views around the corner dont really hurt :)

New driveway and newly added RV parking in the back yard!

Welcome home to this beautiful 3200+ square foot Issaquah property! This 4 BR home boasts large open living spaces, over-sized bedrooms, remodeled baths & windows galore allowing an for an abundance of natural light. Fireplaces in both the living room and family room. Updated kitchen w/granite counters,double ovens & mountain views. Two car garage and huge fully fenced yard. Neighborhood Description

Close to dowtown Issaquah, restaurants, theaters, Historic Gilman Village, salmon hatchery.  Convenient I-90 access for easy commute to Bellevue and Seattle.  Excellent school district.  All of the commonly used stores such as Target, Trader Joe's and Costco are also conveniently located in town.  No freeway driving necessary.
whatownerloves: House has a treehouse feel from the kitchen and family room with views of the surrounding mountains and majestic trees.  Kitchen conveniently located between family room/breakfast bar and the formal dining and living room.  Living and family room both have large brick fireplaces.  Downstairs has access from garage and driveway directly into tiled mudroom for muddy/wet kids and pets.   Large fenced backyard for kids and dogs to run and play.  Separate laundry room with plenty of storage. Laundry chute from upstairs to laundry room.   Basement room for loud, musical kids.  Terrific, kind and quiet neighbors on ALL sides.  Lots of outdoor activities with plenty of designated hiking trails and Lake Samammish close by.  Snoqualmie skiing/boarding 30 minutes east.  School bus route for for all grades directly across the street.   Great community center with lots of activities for kids and adults (such as an indoor walking track) located in downtown.  Also indoor pool open year-round for lessons and recreation.  Downtown has wonderful restaurants and artists studios.  Salmon Festival every year in October hosts lots of food, incredible artists and performances.  Local theater group (Village Theater) hosts musicals and plays.  There is also Kidstage, a kids theater which has classes and performances.  A wonderful music store which offers lessons for all ages in almost every instrument.   Neighborhood has all ages from very small children to teens and retirees.  Dogs are a very welcome addition in this neighborhood.
